properties.GIS_WEB.SDE.PublicFishingTBL.PubWater_Co: Electric motors or non-powered boats allowed. Purchase trout tags at park office. Cost of tag is $6, which allows harvest of four trout. Cabins and camping
properties.GIS_WEB.SDE.PublicFishingTBL.PubWater_Re: Black bass - 21-inch minimum length limit. Lake No. 3 is designated as catch and release for all catfish species.  Open dates for trout fishing will be published and posted. Trout fishing hours 7 a.m. to sunset. Daily trout tag required to attempt to take and to possess trout on entire area from March 1 through June 30.

From Gavins Point Dam to 0.6 miles downstream, a nonresident Nebraska fishing license is required of anglers who are not residents of Nebraska or South Dakota when fishing from a boat or either bank. No crossbows.
